# Frontend Integration Guide: Notes & Transactions

This guide details how to integrate the **Notes (Entries)** and **Len-Den (Transactions)** features into the frontend application.

## Base URL
Ensure all requests are prefixed with your API base URL (e.g., `http://localhost:8000`).
All requests must include the `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.

---

## 1. Notes API (Diary Entries)
**Endpoint**: `/api/v1/entries`

### 1.1 Create a Note
**POST** `/api/v1/entries/`

Create a new diary entry, optionally linking it to one or more contacts.

**Request Body (`EntryCreate`):**
```json
{
  "title": "Lunch with Client",         // Optional: Title of the note
  "content": "Discussed Q1 roadmap...", // Required: The main text body
  "images": [                           // Optional: List of image URLs
    "https://example.com/photo1.jpg"
  ],
  "contact_ids": [                      // Optional: List of Contact UUIDs
    "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-1234-567890abcdef"
  ]
}
```

**Response (`EntryResponse`):**
```json
{
  "id": 101,
  "user_id": "...",
  "title": "Lunch with Client",
  "content": "Discussed Q1 roadmap...",
  "images": [...],
  "created_at": "2024-03-15T12:00:00Z",
  "contacts": [                         // Expanded contact details
    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4...",
      "full_name": "Alice Smith",
      "avatar_url": "..."
    }
  ]
}
```

### 1.2 List Notes
**GET** `/api/v1/entries/?skip=0&limit=20`

Returns a list of notes, sorted by `created_at` (newest first).

### 1.3 Get Note Details
**GET** `/api/v1/entries/{id}`

Returns a single note with its linked contacts.

### 1.4 Update Note
**PATCH** `/api/v1/entries/{id}`

Update fields using `EntryUpdate` schema.
- **Replacing Contacts**: Providing `contact_ids` will **replace** the existing list of linked contacts.

```json
{
  "content": "Updated content...",
  "contact_ids": [] // Passing empty list removes all contact links
}
```

### 1.5 Delete Note
**DELETE** `/api/v1/entries/{id}`

